Reasoning: The paper deals with capacity theorems for a multi-way relay channel, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses coding strategies and their performance, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new coding strategy, which involves signal processing techniques (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of cut-set upper bounds, which is a common technique in communication complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the coding strategies in terms of signal-to-noise ratio, which is a common metric in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
